# FlowPilot v1 - Codex Hard Rules (DO NOT BREAK)

## 1. SYSTEM IDENTITY RULE

This project is NOT:
- AI agent
- automation bot
- RPA system
- browser controller

It is a UI Step State Machine SDK.

---

## 2. SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH RULE

Only ONE module is allowed to control flow:

→ runtime/engine.ts

No other module may:
- decide next step
- mutate workflow state
- trigger transitions

---

## 3. STEP RULE (CRITICAL)

Step is PURE CONFIG ONLY.

Allowed fields:
- id
- type
- highlight
- desc

FORBIDDEN:
- state
- status
- behavior
- runtime logic
- auto actions

---

## 4. BEHAVIOR RULE

behavior/listener.ts is EVENT ONLY.

Allowed:
- DOM event listening
- event normalization
- EventBus emission

FORBIDDEN:
- step decision
- validation
- state mutation
- DOM-based logic decisions

---

## 5. ADAPTER RULE (CRITICAL)

Adapter is the ONLY DOM truth layer.

Allowed:
- DOM query
- element resolution
- UI highlight rendering
- tooltip rendering

FORBIDDEN:
- click()
- fill()
- submit()
- triggering user actions
- flow control logic

---

## 6. RUNTIME RULE

runtime/engine.ts is the ONLY decision maker.

Allowed:
- step transition
- event processing
- recovery trigger
- state update

FORBIDDEN:
- DOM access
- UI rendering
- selector logic
- business logic

---

## 7. RECOVERY RULE

Recovery is a correction layer only.

Allowed:
- detect mismatch
- decide recovery strategy
- reset or remap step state

FORBIDDEN:
- DOM querying
- UI rendering
- step execution logic

---

## 8. VALIDATION RULE

Validation must use Adapter as the ONLY DOM source.

No direct DOM access inside validator or recovery.

---

## 9. FLOW RULE (STRICT)

Execution must follow:

User Action
→ Behavior (normalize only)
→ EventBus
→ Runtime Engine (decision)
→ Validator (via Adapter)
→ Recovery (if needed)
→ Reconcile
→ Adapter (render only)

---

## 10. ANTI-PATTERN RULE (CRITICAL)

DO NOT introduce:
- Executors
- automation scripts
- AI reasoning loops
- self-triggered actions
- hidden flow transitions

---

## 11. ENGINEERING PHILOSOPHY

"Flow is deterministic, UI is observed, not controlled."

Any deviation from determinism is considered a bug in architecture, not a feature.
